comments.body:
You should be able to do:

without esModuleInterop:
```ts
import Onfleet = require('@onfleet/node-onfleet');
import Task = require('@onfleet/node-onfleet/Resources/Task');
// and access Task.CreateTaskProps
```

with esModuleInterop:
```ts
import Onfleet from '@onfleet/node-onfleet';
import { CreateTaskProps } from '@onfleet/node-onfleet/Resources/Task';
```

You could conceivably also nest namespaces together so that they’re all accessible from the index:

```ts
import Onfleet = require('@onfleet/node-onfleet');
type T = Onfleet.Task.CreateTaskProps;
```

but you’d have to be careful that those namespaces _only_ contain types, because the actual `Task` class isn’t going to exist on `Onfleet.Task` at runtime. Not sure those hoops are worth jumping through.
